France ’40 - Rules Summary

Effects Summary

2. Basic Information

2.2. Terrain

  • Marsh River is a Major River.
  • Marsh around a minor River upgrades the hexside to a Major River hexside.
  • Restricted (Hexes): [Wooded Rough / Marsh]
  • German never benefit from Allied Fortified Hexes.

2.3. Counter Information

2.3.4. Unit Type

4. Stacking

  • Can stack up to 7 Stacking Points (SPs).
  • Units of the same division can never be more than 3SPs.
  • Every stack is allowed to have one tank unit with 2- SPs even if exceeding the stacking limit.
  • Stacking Limit can never be exceeded except during [MOV / AAC / Retreat].

5. ZOC

  • ZOCs extend across all hexsides except All-Sea/Tidal River hexsides.
  • HQs and Fort do not exert ZOC.
  • Types: Uncontested / Contested / Negated
  • Entering: Stop upon entering EZOC (No extra cost).
  • Leaving: +2MPs. May move directly from EZOC to EZOC.
  • Losing: Entry Hex / Train / Full Retreat

6. ZOC Bond

  • Eligibility: Good Order & 2+ DEF STR & Exerting ZOC
    • Can form a ZOC Hexside Bond with a friendly map edge.
  • Restriction: Cannot form ZOC Bond if
    • Through City
    • All-Sea/Tidal River hexside
    • Across two Major River hexsides5

7. Movement

7.3. Extended Movement

  • Increase MA by 2/3/4.
  • May not move adj to Enemy.
  • May begin adj from Enemy.

7.4. Tactical Movement

  • All Units can move one or two hexes regardless their MA.
  • May ATK.
  • Abide by movement restrictions.

7.5. Movement & Terrain

  • Roads: allows reduced movement rates
  • Rivers: [+1MP (Non-mehch) / +2MPs (Mech)]. Must adj to cross unbridged Major unless Pontoon. May move normally after crossing.
  • Bridges: [Road (Cancel) / Rail (-1MP)] of crossing costs

7.5.4. Pontoon Bridges

  • Exist at Major River hexside where both sides are occupied by friendly Units; even [one is moving / during AAC / Disrupted / Full Retreat].
  • A unit forming it may move after providing other units crossings.

7.7. Automatic DS

  • Occurs when adj units makes 10-1 (including Tank & TQ Shift). Apply DS.
  • Units not participating can move through the vacated hexes.
  • Procedure: AutoDS on attacking units → cannot move further that Movement Phase → during the next Combat Ph, cannot participate regular combat, but can AAC anytime → remove AutoDS.
  • One stack in each Automatic DS attack may conduct BRK.

7.6. Allied Rail Movement

  • Entraining: Good Order units can entrain at [Town / City] 4+ hexes from German units (May move 2- hexes to reach).
  • Rail Movement (Movement Ph)
    • 15- rail hexes, 3- units per turn
    • Must be [reinforcements / entrained in a previous turn].
    • Hexes traversed must be 4+ hexes from German [unit / controlled City].
    • May not end stacked with other Rail Moved Units.
  • Detraining
    • Replace Train by Disrupted. May detrain in any rail hex.
    • Allied Movement Ph Begin: [Voluntarily / Find itself 4- hexes of Enemy]
    • Anytime: If forced to retreat

7.6.2. Train Effects

  • May not ATK / 1 DEF STR / No ZOC
  • No Terrain benefit if alone / No Tank Shift.
  • HQ: Cannot [Ready / Shift].
  • Detrain immediately if forced to retreat.

7.7. Automatic DS

  • [Tank / TQ] Shifts may be used but not [Air / HQ] Shifts.
  • Apply DS during Movement Ph if 10-1 Odd is made.
  • Procedure: Place AutoDS (stop moving) → AAC anytime during Combat Ph

8. Combat

  • Need not pre-declare all.
  • There exist 8-1 and 9-1 columns identical to 7-1.
  • Procedure: Compute STR Odds → Apply Shifts → dr
  • Maximum STR: 20 Defense after [halving / doubling]. 40 Attack before halving.
  • Allied Cooperation: French, British and Belgian units may stack and defend together, but may not attack together.
  • Selecting Step losses
    • Infrantry Remnants are the last steps to be lost.
    • Within a German [Panzer / Motorized] divisions, a full strength unit must be selected over a reduced unit if they are stacked together.

9. Combat Modifiers

9.1. Halving & Doubling

  • Never be havled nor doubled more than once.
  • If both havled and doubled, use printed STR.
  • Applies to individual unit and round up
    • Exception: 1-STR units are added up and then halved.
  • Halving
    • ATK STR: OOS / across Major River / across Maginot Line / out of Restricted
    • DEF STR: Disrupted
  • Doubling
    • DEF STR: All attackers [across Rivers / out of Restricted]

9.2. Combat Shifts

  • One favorable column shift for either ATK or DEF
  • Tank: DEF Terrain permitting, one column shift if only one side has Tanks.
    • ATK [across Rivers / out of Restricted] cannot provide Tank Shift, but deny DEF shift except Heavy Tanks.
    • French 2-1-6 tank cannot deny German Tank Shift.
  • Heavy Tank: DEF Terrain permitting, Tank Shift regardless enemy tanks.
  • Air Support: Max 1 per attack (except GT1 Sickle Cut)
  • HQ: Max 1 per attack
  • Elite Combined Arms: Elite Tank and Inf stacked together
  • Low Quality Units: if all participating units are Low Quality

11. Determined Defense

  • With Eligible Lead Unit to cancel Retreat portion except Full Retreats.
  • Eligible Lead Unit: Good Order (Fort Unit if possible)
    • Not HQ nor Entrained.
  • Single Step Defender: If eliminated after a successful DD, the attacker may advance into the Vacated (only) and stop.
    • If the DEF hex still contains units (HQ, Disrupted, ..) then the hex holds.
  • French Collapse: if Lead Unit is French and OOS at the moment of DD.
  • DD Air Support: German only. Max 1 per DD. Air Unit spent on Defensive Support can provide DD Air Support at no extra cost.

11.4. Desperate Defense

  • Allowed if [Eliminated if retreat / Port & Losing it force OOS after retreat].
  • Must choose either DD or Desperate Defense before any roll.
  • Lead Unit may be selected for each attempt.
  • The DD Air Support DRM is applied to every roll.
  • Restriction: Cannot perform on [DS / DR4].
  • Procedure
    1. Attempt DD as usual manner
    2. Fail of any type → “-/1”
    3. Try again until [Retreat cancelled / All DEF eliminiated]

12. Retreats

  • Friendly Unit negates EZOC it occupies unless retreated current combat
  • Retreating through friendly units do not disturb non-retreating units.
  • May enter contested EZOC (Not two consecutives).
  • Direction Guideline (Must follow in the order of priority)
    1. No same hex twice. No zig-zag
    2. Avoid step losses
    3. X hexes away from departing hex (Lose a step for each unfulfilled)
    4. In Supply position
  • Over-stacking
    • May end overstacked, but must resolve the owner’s next Movement Ph
    • If force to retreat again in the same Ph, elimininated.

12.2. Eliminated If

  • Uncontested EZOC except the first hex of the retreat
  • Two consecutive EZOCs
  • Off Map / Prohibited / ZOC Bond / Major River (even if bridge)
  • Ending in EZOC (May retreat exactly one more hex to avoid eliminiation, but it is not allowed for after two consecutive EZOCs).

12.4. Stopping a Retreat

  • If ALL the following conditions are met:
    • Retreated 1+ hexes
    • Not ending in EZOC unless a friendly non-disrupted already in the hex
    • Into [City / Fortified (Allied only)]
  • Early Stoppiing does not affect [AAC result / Disruption / Full Retreat].

13. Disruption & Recovery

13.2. Distrupted

  • Not affected: ZOC / TQ / Tank Shift
  • Limited: TAC MOV only / DEF STR Halved
  • Restricted: ZOC Bond / ATK / HQ Shift or Readying
  • Units may [enter / pass] through friendly Disrupted units without affected.

13.3. Full Retreat

  • When
    • DR4 or DS
    • Disrupted & Forced to retreat
    • Voluntarily when Disrupted or GQG (friendly Movement Ph)
  • Movement: Full MA. May use Extended Movement.
    • Benefit: No extra cost for leaving EZOC
  • Restricted:
    • Lose ZOCs
    • ATK / DEF / HQ Shift / HQ Ready
    • Entering EZOC unless negated
    • Cannot enter Enemy controlled City
    • Adj to Enemy
      • Must retreat 2 hexes unless in a hex with non-Disrupted
      • The Enemy may then continue [moving / advancing / retreating]

13.4. Recovery

  • dr if EZOC, automatic otherwise.
  • Full Retreat may choose not to recover.

14. AAC

  • Units stacked together but not participating the attack can AAC together.
  • Except Limited Advance, may advance in any direction.
  • No need to enter the Vacated.
  • Stop upon entering EZOC (even if negated) unless the Vacated.
  • Stop upon crossing a Major River even if bridged
    • May only cross during the first hex of AAC.
  • Cannot enter [Restricted / Prohibited].

15. Breakthrough Combat

  • Breakthrough Group:
    • Forming with eligibles, applying Stacking Limit & Allied Cooperation.
    • May form in the Vacated.
    • Can drop off units from the BRK Group. The dropped end their AAC.
  • Remember BRK Costs & Shifts.
  • No [HQ / Air] Shifts for both sides
    • Exception: DD Air already in presence
  • Procedure: Declare a BRK Group → AAC & BRK → Other’s AAC
  • If Fails to [vacate / force retreat] → End the AAC.
  • If Success, continue the AAC from [Launched / Vacated].
    • Enters the Vacated at no extra cost.
    • End in the Vacated but EZOC → [End / Try another to free itself]
  • Unlike retreats from regular Combat, units that have already retreated may defend against BRK combat and are not eliminated if forced to retreat again; if overstacked, the defender choose some not to contribute.
  • No Additional Hexes: do not earn additional AAC allowance (use initial ATK’s).

17. Allied HQs

  • To provide HQ Shift, the HQ must 7- hexes to participating friendly unit and have the same nationality of one of the participating units.
  • TAC MOV only if Ready, or Flip to Used for full (Mech) MA.
  • Retreat 2 hexes and Disrupted if adj to Enemy
    • Full Retreat if already Disrupted.
    • Eliminated if cannot retreat.
  • Allied Initial Ph: May Ready if [Good Order & LOS to Entry except X/N].
  • Allied Supply Ph: No Attrition roll. Eliminated if [OOS & no LOS to non-HQ Unit].

18. Supply

  • Check LOS during Owner’s Supply Ph → In Supply or OOS
  • Supply Source: See Scenario rules
  • Allied Units tracing LOS to three friendly controlled Cities is In Supply.

18.3. Line of Supply

  • 5- Overland Hexes, and then, ∞ Road Hexes
    • [Wood Rough / Marsh] costs 2 Overland hexes.
  • Restrictions: LOS cannot enter or pass
    • All-Sea/Tidal River
    • Enemy [occupied hex / controlled City / ZOC Bond]
    • EZOC (Friendly units negate EZOC they occupy for LOS); Overland Portion may enter contested EZOC (Not two consecutives).

18.4. Effects: OOS

  • Not affected: ZOC / DEF STR / TQ / Tank Shift
  • Limited: TAC MOV only / ATK STR Halved / Max AAC: 2
  • Prohibited: Replacements

18.5. Isolation Attrition

  • dr each unit if red OOS
  • Exception: HQ / Not adj to Enemy / Overland LOS of any length / Fort Unit stacked or adj to non-Fort Unit (Fort itself provides +2 DRM)
  • May lose the last step.

19. Reinforcements

  • Entry Hex is not playable. Reinforcements may not remain in those hexes or attack from them. Closed if Good Order Enemy exit the Entry.
    • May use EXT MOV to exit Entry.
  • Movement Ph: Through Entry paying TEC cost of the first hex entered; May reinforce on ZOC but stop; delayed to the following turn if the Entry not allowed.
    • May use full MA on arrival.
  • Allied (Sickle Cut): Random draw as per TRT. See Reinforcement areas on the counters. Place one per hex if possible; two if not allowed. May delay to enter via adj Entry Area by Strategic Rail Movement; Place Train.
  • German: Max one division on each Entry per turn; May 2 or 3 units constitute one division, not applicable to indep battalion (may enter with a division). Area A-# are available once some enters on the areas.

20. Special Rules

  • Recon Unit: Yellow DEF STR. Ignores step loss of [D1 / DS] if attacked alone.
  • Rommel: For each time [ATK / DEF / BRK / Lead DD], allowed one re-roll each.
  • Montgomery: If defending in Good Order, allowed one re-roll for each [CRT / DD]; Rommel decide rerolling first if both present.
  • Disengagement (ATK): Good Orders may attempt Disengagement ATK once during any point of friendly Combat Ph. dr for each [Unit / Group] by Owner’s choice. Retreat 2- hexes (and Disrupted) in any direction if successful.

21. Sickle Cut Scenario

  • German Supply Source: Entry [A / B / C / D]
  • Allied Supply Source: Entry [X / N / W / S / SE / E]
  • The Dyle Line
    • Finish construction at GT1 Allied Movement Ph End, if at least one Inf start there and stay there.
    • Removed upon [DD results / unit in the hex are eliminated or force to retreat / no friendly units present at Owner’s Supply Ph End].
  • German Mass Air Strike: Max 3 Air Support in a single combat on GT1
  • Additional Turn (Optional): Upon agreement at the game start, on GT10, player with 5+VP pay 3VP to extend the game one additional turn.

21.2. GQG

  • Grand Quartier General (GQG) slow down and prevent ATK.
  • Any Ph End: Suffer GQG if stacked with; but can pass through without affected.
  • Units Exempt: HQ, de Gaulle; They may freely exit and pass through GQG.
  • Return to Holding Box if [Disrupted / sent into Full Retreat (except GT1)].

21.2.1. Effects: GQG

  • Not affected: ZOC / TQ / Tank / DEF STR / Lead DD
  • Limited: TAC MOV only
  • Prohibited: ATK / Disengagement / Stack split / Stop voluntarily in a hex containing GQG (Allowed for a while upon inevitable situation of Retreats but resolve ASAP.)

21.2.4. GQG Phase

  • Procedure: Place one per 1+ French Hex (even on Train) → Return 2- (DR)
  • How Many: 6 (GT1) / Remainings of Holding Box (since GT2)
  • Return to Holding Box: If GQG stack [Eliminated / Disrupted / Full Retreat]
  • Scheduled Removal: GT3+, before placement during GQG Ph, remove one in the numerical order per turn from play (1→2→…).

21.3. Rundstedt’s Halt!

  • When: Once per game, any turn GT5+, during Allied Supply Ph.
  • How: Place 6- Halt markers on hexes containing 1+ German Mech; selected must be West further than all German non-Mech divisions. 3- hexes from German non-Mech cannot be selected.
  • After placement, two dr to remove the markers matching the each dr.
  • Effect: Same as GQG. Last for one German turn; remove after.

21.7. Victory Condition

  • The player with the most Victory Points at the end of the game wins.

21.7.1. Allied VPs

  • 10VP if railroad connection between [X / N] and [S / W]
    • Must be free from German Unit or EZOC
  • 5VP if no railroad connection, but can trace LOS from [X / N] to [S / W]
  • 1VP per multi-step German Unit Eliminated
  • 1VP per multi-step German Mech with no LOS of any length

21.7.2. German VPs

  • 10VP if Allied rail connection fails.
  • 1VP for each Allied Entry closed (2VP for S/SE near Reim)
    • Must LOS at the Game End
  • 1VP per German exited Entry X
    • Must trace LOS at the instant of exit

21.8. French Restriction

  • French Army Boundary (GT1)
    • French north of the Sambre-Meuse line inclusive may not cross to the south of that line (1st Army/9th Army boundary line). 1st DCR is exempt.
    • French south of the Aisne-Canal des Ardennes Line may not cross to the north of that line (9th Army/2nd Army boundary line).
  • Allied Random Reinforcements Delay
    • GT2-5: N and S are delayed by 1 and 2 turns, respectively.
    • GT6-9: S are delayed by 1 turn.

22. Dynamo Scenario

22.1 Setup

  • Game Length: 12 turns (5/24-6/4)
  • First Player: German
  • Map: Dynamo map.
  • Setup: Use the Dynamo At Start Cards
  • Halt! Markers: Allied places six markers before the game begins → dr 2 to remove 2-
  • Supply Source
    • German: Any East or South Map Edge Hex.
    • Allied: Allied Port / to three Cities
  • City Control: German controls all City hexes outside the Allied pocket.

22.2 Halt! Order

  • Effective during GT 1-3. Basically same as in Sickle Cut
  • Allied Supply Ph: Place remaining Halt! on GT 1 and 2 (dr 2 to remove 2-).
  • Halt! markers are placed on Panzer divisions.
    • Two Panzer division under “May Not Move” are exempt.
    • 1st Panzer Division may not be targeted until it clears Calais of Allied Units.
    • Other units stacked with Panzer division under a Halt! are not affected.
  • During GT 1-3, all German Panzer divisions must remain stacked together even those without Halt! markers.
  • If Disrupted, replace Halt! by Disrupted (or Full Retreat).

22.3 Replacements

  • GT 1-3 German Initial Ph: In Supply Good Order German Panzer divisions get one replacement of any kind each turn.

22.4 Belgian Units

  • Surrender (Any Allied Initial Ph): If [Brugge is German controlled / GT5], remove all.
  • Movement Restriction: May not enter France. Eliminated if forced to retreat. May stay in border hexes.

22.5 Allied Evacuations

  • Allied Initial Ph of GT4+, dr for one Port and dr for two beaches to evacuate Units.
  • If no Allied Units in Dunkirk, May evacuate Units from [Calais / Oostende].

22.7 Special Rules

  • Air: German 3, Allied 2
  • Allied HQ: Used side (cannot be flipped). 1VP per evacuation.
  • German Reinforcements: Arrived on south map edge half hexes.
  • German Movement Restriction: 2nd and 10th Panzer Divisions cannot move or attack but can defense at full. 1st Panzer Division is released when Calais is cleared. It may attack Calais each turn and may advance into Calais when cleared of Enemy. Operates normally after that.
  • No rail movements. No GQG.
  • German Withdrawls: GT6+, see TRT

22.8 Terrain in Dynamo

  • Polder: No Tank Shift. Costs 1MP for all Units.
  • Ferry Hexsides: Spend entire MA to across. No combat allowed.
  • Causeway Hex: Costs 1MP for all Units. DEF double.
  • Tidal River Bridges: +1MP to cross. No attack across.

22.9 0-STR Remnant

  • All British Combat Units with DEF 3+ of their last step have one additional 0-0-3 step.
  • May voluntarily shed steps to become 0-0-3
  • Full Retreat permanantly
  • Non-mech
  • 1VP per evacuation

22.10 Victory Conditions

  • Allied Automatic Victory: immediately if evacuates or moves off the west or south map edge, 15+ units (10+ British).
  • End Game Victory: Allied wins if 15+ VP, otherwise German victory
    • 1VP for each British/French unit evacuated or moved off the west or south map edge
    • 1VP for each French unit In Supply still on the map
    • 1VP for each German multi-step unit eliminated
    • -1VP for each British unit eliminated or still on the map
